{{pp-move-indef}}{{calendar}}
{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

This day marks the approximate midpoint of summer in the [[Northern Hemisphere]] and of winter in the [[Southern Hemisphere]] (starting the season at the June solstice).

==Events==
*[[322 BC]] &ndash; [[Battle of Crannon]] between [[Athens]] and Macedon.
* [[461]] &ndash; Roman Emperor [[Majorian]] is beheaded near the river [[Staffora|Iria]] in north-west Italy following his arrest and deposition by the ''magister militum'' [[Ricimer]].
* [[626]] &ndash; The [[Eurasian Avars|Avar]] and [[Slavic peoples|Slav]] armies leave the [[siege of Constantinople (626)|siege of Constantinople]].
* [[936]] &ndash; Coronation of King [[Otto I, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto I of Germany]].
*[[1420]] &ndash; Construction of the dome of [[Florence Cathedral|Santa Maria del Fiore]] begins in [[Florence]].
*[[1427]] &ndash; The [[House of Visconti|Visconti]] of Milan's fleet is destroyed by the [[Republic of Venice|Venetians]] on the [[Po (river)|Po River]].
*[[1461]] &ndash; The [[Ming Dynasty]] [[Military history of China before 1911|Chinese military general]] Cao Qin [[Rebellion of Cao Qin|stages a coup]] against the [[Zhengtong Emperor|Tianshun Emperor]].
*[[1679]] &ndash; The [[brigantine]] ''[[Le Griffon]]'', commissioned by [[René-Robert Cavelier, Sieur de La Salle]], is towed to the south-eastern end of the [[Niagara River]], to become the first ship to sail the upper [[Great Lakes]] of [[North America]].
*[[1714]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Gangut]]: the first important victory of the [[Russian Navy]].
*[[1782]] &ndash; [[George Washington]] orders the creation of the [[Badge of Military Merit]] to honor soldiers wounded in battle. It is later renamed to the more poetic [[Purple Heart]].
*[[1789]] &ndash; The [[United States Department of War]] is established.
*[[1791]] &ndash; American troops destroy the [[Miami people|Miami]] town of [[Battle of Kenapacomaqua|Kenapacomaqua]] near the site of present-day [[Logansport, Indiana]] in the [[Northwest Indian War]].
*[[1794]] &ndash; [[President of the United States|U.S. President]] George Washington invokes the [[Militia Acts of 1792]] to suppress the [[Whiskey Rebellion]] in [[western Pennsylvania]].
*[[1819]] &ndash; [[Simón Bolívar]] triumphs over [[Spain]] in the [[Battle of Boyacá]].
*[[1879]] &ndash; The opening of the [[Openshaw Citadel|Poor Man's Palace]] in [[Manchester|Manchester, England]].
*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Anna Månsdotter]] becomes the last woman in [[Sweden]] to be executed, for the 1889 [[Yngsjö murder]].
*[[1909]] &ndash; [[Alice Huyler Ramsey]] and three friends become the first women to complete a transcontinental auto trip, taking 59 days to travel from [[New York City|New York, New York]] to [[San Francisco|San Francisco, California]].
*[[1927]] &ndash; The [[Peace Bridge]] opens between [[Fort Erie, Ontario]] and [[Buffalo, New York]].
*[[1930]] &ndash; The last confirmed [[lynching]] of blacks in the Northern United States occurs in [[Marion, Indiana]]. Two men, [[Thomas Shipp and Abram Smith]], are killed.
*[[1933]] &ndash; The [[Simele massacre]]: The [[Politics of Iraq|Iraqi government]] [[Simele massacre|slaughters]] over 3,000 [[Assyrian people|Assyrians]] in the village of [[Simele]]. The day becomes known as Assyrian Martyrs Day.
*[[1938]] &ndash; [[The Holocaust]]: The building of [[Mauthausen-Gusen concentration camp|Mauthausen concentration camp]] begins.
*[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Alsace-Lorraine]] is annexed by the Third Reich.
*[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: the [[Guadalcanal Campaign|Battle of Guadalcanal]] begins &ndash; [[United States Marine Corps|United States Marines]] initiate the first American offensive of the war with landings on [[Guadalcanal]] and [[Battle of Tulagi and Gavutu–Tanambogo|Tulagi]] in the [[Solomon Islands]].
*[[1944]] &ndash; [[IBM]] dedicates the first program-controlled [[calculator]], the Automatic Sequence Controlled Calculator (known best as the [[Harvard Mark I]]).
*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Thor Heyerdahl]]'s [[Ochroma pyramidale|balsa wood]] raft the [[Kon-Tiki]], smashes into the [[reef]] at [[Raroia]] in the [[Tuamotus|Tuamotu Islands]] after a 101-day, {{Convert|7000|km|mi}} journey across the [[Pacific Ocean]] in an attempt to prove that pre-historic peoples could have traveled from [[South America]].
*  1947   &ndash; The [[Municipal Corporation of Greater Mumbai|Bombay Municipal Corporation]] formally takes over the [[Brihanmumbai Electric Supply and Transport|Bombay Electric Supply and Transport]] (BEST).
*[[1955]] &ndash; [[Sony|Tokyo Telecommunications Engineering]], the precursor to [[Sony]], sells its first [[transistor radio]]s in [[Japan]].
*[[1959]] &ndash; The [[Lincoln Memorial]] design on the U.S. [[Penny (United States coin)|penny]] goes into circulation. It replaces the "sheaves of wheat" design, and was minted until 2008.
*  1959   &ndash; [[Explorer program]]: ''[[Explorer 6]]'' launches from the [[Eastern Range|Atlantic Missile Range]] in [[Cape Canaveral, Florida]].
*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Côte d'Ivoire]] becomes independent from France.
*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: the [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] passes the [[Gulf of Tonkin Resolution]] giving U.S. President [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] broad war powers to deal with [[North Vietnam]]ese attacks on American forces.
*[[1965]] &ndash; The infamous first Reyes party between [[Ken Kesey]]'s [[Merry Pranksters]] and motorcycle gang the [[Hells Angels]] takes place at Kesey's estate in [[La Honda, California]] introducing psychedelics to the gang world and forever linking the [[hippie]] movement to the Hell's Angels.
*[[1966]] &ndash; [[List of ethnic riots|Race riot]]s occur in [[Lansing, Michigan]].
*[[1970]] &ndash; California judge [[Harold Haley]] is taken hostage in his courtroom and killed during an effort to free [[George Jackson (Black Panther)|George Jackson]] from police custody.
*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Philippe Petit]] performs a high wire act between the twin towers of the [[World Trade Center]] {{Convert|1368|ft|m}} in the air.
*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Viking program]]: ''[[Viking 2]]'' enters orbit around [[Mars]].
*[[1978]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Jimmy Carter]] declares a federal emergency at [[Love Canal]] due to [[toxic waste]] that had been negligently disposed of.
*[[1979]] &ndash; [[1979 Woodstock, Ontario tornado|Several tornadoes]] strike the city of [[Woodstock, Ontario]], [[Canada]] and the surrounding communities.
*[[1981]] &ndash; ''[[The Washington Star]]'' ceases all operations after 128 years of publication.
*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Takao Doi]], [[Mamoru Mohri]] and [[Chiaki Mukai]] are chosen to be Japan's first [[astronaut]]s.
*  1985   &ndash; The [[White House Farm murders]] took place near the English village of [[Tolleshunt D'Arcy]], [[Essex|Essex, England]].
*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Lynne Cox]] becomes first person to swim from the [[United States]] to the [[Soviet Union]], crossing from [[Little Diomede Island]] in Alaska to [[Big Diomede]] in the Soviet Union
*[[1989]] &ndash; U.S. Congressman [[Mickey Leland]] (D-[[Texas|TX]]) and 15 others die in a [[Aviation accidents and incidents|plane crash]] in [[Ethiopia]].
*[[1998]] &ndash; [[1998 United States embassy bombings|The United States embassy bombings]] in [[Dar es Salaam]], [[Tanzania]] and [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]] kill approximately 212 people.
*[[1999]] &ndash; The [[Chechnya]]-based [[Islamic International Brigade]] [[Invasion of Dagestan (1999)|invades]] the neighboring Russian [[Dagestan]].
*[[2007]] &ndash; [[Barry Bonds]] of the [[San Francisco Giants]] breaks [[baseball]] great [[Hank Aaron]]'s record by hitting his 756th [[home run]].
*[[2008]] &ndash; [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] launches a large-scale military offensive against [[South Ossetia]], in an attempt to reclaim the territory from [[Russia]], starting the [[2008 South Ossetia war]].
*[[2012]] &ndash; Three gunmen [[Deeper Life Church shooting|kill 19 people]] in a church near [[Okene]], [[Nigeria]].

